  {
    "client_msg_id": "448e7e29-7e71-44aa-8a2a-7d324236771a",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "<@UA14TGLTC> um in what perspective?\n\nThis is indeed quite nice field of rabbit holes. For example data model itself can be just local json or full sematinc web etc.\n\nText (CLI) is human and machine-readable but I would say it's human-first data. You can write your stuff and most people can understand that but for computer it's just list (or grid) of meaningless numbers.\n\nBeing human-first means that we are the ones who have to explain data to computer: write parsers, general text cannot be visalized much better and so on. Planning \"smarter\" data is about flipping data to be machine-first =&gt; it should be computers job to explain data to us.\n\nI really hope that I have time to make some better demo at summer besides writing (and relaxing from day job).",
    "user": "U7C7B75R6",
    "ts": "1528496930.000236",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
